The course gives an overview of the history of the Western (and to a lesser extent also Eastern) churches. The following themes are discussed: development of church organisation; formation of certain aspects of ecclesiastical law; relationships between ecclesiastical and secular powers; the major philosophical and doctrinal views; forms and culture of Christian spirituality.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of the history of Christianity.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  At the end of the course students: * have aquired basic understandig of the historical processes in the Christianity * are able to discern main historical and doctrinal developments * are able to recognize and apply most important terminology * connect historical and doctrinal developments into a unified process.
